<task id="010" project="file-preview-dialog-with-auth-enhancements">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create FilePreviewDialog Component</title>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>fluent-ui, dialog, component</tags>
    <estimate>3-4 hours</estimate>
    <dependencies>007</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Create FilePreviewDialog.tsx with Fluent UI v9 Dialog shell, title bar, toolbar layout, and iframe preview area</goal>
    <context>
      FilePreviewDialog is the standardized file preview component for LegalWorkspace. It replaces
      the ad-hoc popover preview in DocumentCard and the 3-button action pattern in FindSimilarResultsStep.
      The dialog provides a consistent preview experience with a title bar showing the document name,
      a toolbar with 4 action buttons (Open File, Open Record, Copy Link, Workspace Toggle), and an
      iframe-based preview area. It uses Fluent UI v9 Dialog primitives and follows ADR-021.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST use Fluent UI v9 Dialog/DialogSurface/DialogBody per ADR-021
      - MUST NOT hard-code colors; use Fluent tokens for theming and dark mode support
      - MUST use @spaarke/auth for authenticated API calls (via DocumentApiService)
      - MUST sandbox iframe with allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-forms allow-popups
      - MUST handle loading, error, and success states gracefully
      - MUST support ESC key to close dialog (Fluent Dialog default behavior)
      - Dialog size: 85vw x 85vh, max-width 880px
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/services/DocumentApiService.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/custom-dialogs-in-dataverse.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/RecordCards/DocumentCard.tsx</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read DocumentCard.tsx for existing preview pattern (popover + iframe approach)</step>
    <step>Read DocumentApiService.ts for getDocumentPreviewUrl() signature and response shape</step>
    <step>Create src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/ directory</step>
    <step>Create FilePreviewDialog.tsx with IFilePreviewDialogProps interface: { open, documentId, documentName, onClose, isInWorkspace?, onWorkspaceFlagChanged? }</step>
    <step>Implement Fluent UI v9 Dialog shell with DialogSurface sized at 85vw x 85vh (max 880px)</step>
    <step>Implement title bar with document name and close button (DismissRegular icon)</step>
    <step>Implement Toolbar layout with 4 ToolbarButton placeholders (Open File, Open Record, Copy Link, Workspace Toggle)</step>
    <step>Implement preview iframe area with sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-forms allow-popups"</step>
    <step>Add state management: previewUrl, isLoadingPreview, previewError, isPinned, isPinning, copySuccess</step>
    <step>Add useEffect to fetch preview URL via DocumentApiService.getDocumentPreviewUrl() when dialog opens</step>
    <step>Implement loading state with Fluent Spinner centered in preview area</step>
    <step>Implement error state with error message and retry button</step>
    <step>Verify TypeScript compiles without errors (tsc --noEmit)</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>FilePreviewDialog.tsx created with correct IFilePreviewDialogProps interface</criterion>
    <criterion>Dialog renders at 85vw x 85vh with max-width 880px using Fluent UI v9</criterion>
    <criterion>Title bar shows document name and close button</criterion>
    <criterion>Toolbar renders 4 ToolbarButton placeholders</criterion>
    <criterion>iframe preview area renders with correct sandbox attributes</criterion>
    <criterion>Loading spinner shows while fetching preview URL</criterion>
    <criterion>Error state displays with retry option on fetch failure</criterion>
    <criterion>ESC key closes the dialog</criterion>
    <criterion>TypeScript compiles without errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
